pageContext.claim: “I just went to Missouri where they had 25,000 people standing outside of 12,000 people in the hall. You saw that, you probably read it. I don't know if they write that. But you know we had 25,000 people outside.”
pageContext.analysis: The Springfield police reported that at least 12,000 people showed up and the Springfield News-Leader reported 20,000 people had signed up to attend the rally. Regardless, there's no evidence that anywhere close to 37,000 people showed up — which would be nearly one-third of Springfield's population.
